comment: Professor Gold's greatest strength is in his lecturing ability. His lectures are interesting, insightful, and knowledgable. He is also very comedic. My class with him was early but I never didn't look forward to go! Highly recommended.

I took professor Gold for MHC1+MHC2. He is wonderful and his cranky attitude towards everything is kind of hilarious. He is brilliant. Yes, the 40+ page paper you have to write each semester is extremely stressful but for MHC1 give yourself a week and for MHC2 take two weeks. I've learned so much from him, he really is a wonderful professor and man

Great Class! Be prepared to work hard though. Three textbooks to read and a major paper due at the end of the semester. Dr. Gold has a wealth of knowledge that he shares willingly with the class. Pay attention - you'll be a better therapist/psychologist for it.

Doctor Gold is hilarious and overall a great guy. His lectures are incredibly interesting. He does expect you to put in a good amount of work and do all of the readings, but he is extremely intelligent and I have learned a lot from him.

Gold is great and does care if you put in the time to be there and participate. He loves it when students participate and has great stories to help explain concepts in class. He is great for advice and definately will go the extra mile to help if you reach out to him. I have taken all possible classes with him but i wish i could take more!

I LOVE Professor Gold. He's hysterically cranky and tells amazing stories. He really knows a lot about psychology and has tons of experience. If you put work into his classes you'll do very well. Tests aren't too hard if you do the work.

Deff. one of my favorite professors at Adelphi. He knows so much about clinical psych and has this charming way of speaking where everything rolls off his tongue smoothly. Doesn't use powerpoints and doesn't really write anything on the board, so take notes! Simply walks around and talks. But don't worry, hes hilarious and pleasant to listen to!

Dr. Gold  is a hilarious guy. He knows what he's talking about and expects the students to have some idea of what they're talking about as well. He only grades by attendance, mid term and final, but the final is a take home and the midterm was easy as well. You don't HAVE to read before every class, but the textbook  is important for the tests!

Great professor. This year, he wanted to help people of different learning styles and allowed students to take the actual midterm/final or make their own midterm/final. I chose to make the two tests and it was such hard work but worth it. I was able to show just how much I learned.  Also, participation really matters in this class.

One of the BEST professors at Adelphi, I highly suggest taking him. Make sure you come to class with questions or he will make his tests fill in, rather than multiple choice. BEST PROFESSOR I feel I have ever had. Also make sure you study because he gives only a midterm and final, 2 unexcused absences allowed and extra credit is an option.
Good class.  Clear expectations from the professor and interesting material.  I especially like the way the professor presented the material. Would definitely recommend taking this class.

I'm very mixed about Gold. I love how he teaches and he's honestly not an awful professor. I just hate the structure of his syllabus. His midterm/final is fill in and maybe I wasn't prepared for his format. I still don't know if I'm happy or not with my decision to take this class with him. He's very helpful, knows his stuff, and I enjoy his humor.
BRILLIANT

Excellent professor. Favorite class of the semester. Funny, sarcastic, story-teller, relevant. Participation opt-out of midterm has never made me read more for class and learn my stuff. Start of class is a lil' annoying because eager participation-point-seeking students ask silly questions. But overall a great class and professor.

This professor is very clear, funny, interesting, and uses lots of real world examples from his own practice. He lets you skip out on the midterm if you like your participation grade midway through. He does expect you to do the reading, but it really just affects your participation grade & will bite you in the butt come the final. Would take again!

He taught an honors seminar this semester. Great class! Learned a LOT. Impossible to gauge his grading though when 50% is the final paper and 50% is participation...fortunately he was pretty lenient. Would definitely take again!
Gold is a really nice guy and he knows his stuff, but his tests were hard. I know my stuff and had a lot of trouble. No one has gotten 100 on his tests.

Fantastic professor.  Great sense of humor and extremely clear.  Fair, as well.  Gives plenty of notice for assignments (like, a whole semester's worth of notice) and final assignment is a cinch.  Given the chance, I'd definitely take another class with him.

one of the most intelligent people ive ever met.clarifies everything and can answer any question you throw at him.if you take notes/pay attention in class youll do fine..be sure to ask questions participation counts

Great Professor if psychology is your field of interest.  He has tons of interesting stories; personal and professional. Is able to clarify most everything if you're confused and is not a harsh grader. One of the best if not the best psychology professor I've had at Adelphi.

Prof Gold is probably one of my favorite professors at Adelphi.  He has a lot of interesting stories and a great sense of humor.  If you take good notes and use the textbook to study, the test are not too bad.  He gives extra credit which makes it possible to get an A.  Overall great professor.

good class.. but on a personal level this guy blows. he doesnt care about his students at all, and hes really condescending. However, hes pretty smart and as long as you dont plan on him helping you out in any way, hes okay

many people find him obnoxious - however if you respect him and show up to class prepared, he is very helpful and respectful.  has tons of interesting stories from his early years as a psychologist and really a great professor for those who take psychology seriously.
He is exactly what professor should be: is able to explain most confusing concepts,to decrease anxiety among students, be strict but fair and kind, make learning enjoyable.
Major Jerk!!!

hes probably the biggest jerk ive ever met my entire life. isnt helpful AT ALL! he doesnt care about the 'regular' students. im quite positive he focuses more on those who are involved with the psych dept, and research....
never took a class with him, but him being the chair of the department..he is a JERK! not helpful at all and this is coming from many experiences with him, and many others will say the same

I took as many classes with him as I could.He is one of the best professors I've ever had and he truly cares about students. Is soo funny and he is a fair grader. Mutual respect is definitely given with him. As far as psych is concerned HE IS THE BEST at Adelphi!!!
No Comments

Good teacher a little tough though but good teacher with VERY interesting stories about running around hospitals chasing his patient who had a fear of being stabbed.. with sissors. HA how great is that.
Eh, the university wouldn't be missing anything if Gold wasn't there to teach.  A bit arrogant and patrionizing, but I guess when you're that intelligent you're allowed to be.

Dr Gold is by far the most amazing professor at Adelphi!  Can't be a psych major w/o having taken at LEAST 2 classes if not MANY more with him!  I only was able to take psychopath &  adolescent with him, but he made each class fun and worth going to!  He knows sooo much and encourages the involvement of all.  He's really helpful 2! Gotta luv him!

Wow, he is an amazing professor. His lectures were very interesting. I must say I walked out of each class with much more knowledge. Multiple choice exams a little tricky but always has plenty of extra credit! Take him!

Dr. Gold is one of the BEST (if not *the* best) psychology professors at Adelphi. I learned so much from him and I can't wait to take more classes with him. Definitely take any of his classes if you get the chance -- you won't regret it.
No Comments
This was a great class, Gold made it even better, you can not stop taking classes with him, he just knows it best and will always cover the course content with a reality-perspective!
great professor, Ive taken a few classes w/ him, he isnt an easy grader but he knows his stuff and if you dont mind his dry personality you'll love his classes. he was actually my favorite
Comes across as very condescending.
I can't believe he is actually a psychologist. I feel bad for his patients.
A very helpful and funny guy, his stories will keep you awake, outside class, he seems to be fazed out, always!
This guy is the most biased person I've ever met.Extremely moody and picks favorites, abuses power I cannot stand this man.  Needs to be retired.

I have taken several classes with this professor. He is  hysterical and will always keep you wanting more. He is not the easiest grader but his classes are the best. I could not stand to graduate without taking one more class with this sexy man.
He is an amazing professor! You can't miss to take a class with this man, very willingly helpful and you will never leave his class without cracking your ribs at least twice!

I have taken four classes with him and each one was great.  I learned a lot and he has some funny stories.  Not an easy grader but you will get a lot out of his classes.  He really cares about the students.
No Comments
Moody.... but he knows his stuff!! You'll learn a great deal in his class.  May need some prozac of his own.
No Comments

She is a great professor! She is highly intelligent and does not stand for stupidity so the people who do not like her are typically the idiots. She can be overwhelming at time and even intimidating but overall her teaching is remarkable.

Overall an amazing teacher. She was funny and personable, and expected a lot from her students, not for her sake but for our sake. She taught me tons not only about experimental psych. but random pieces of info. VIGNETTE.
Professor Austin is tough, and you need to work hard in her class, but I have never learned more from a professor.
easy to fool

Horrible teacher had her for social psych just took it for an elective was a horrible idea. Not to say you shouldn't work for your grade but you have to work so hard for that stupid class just to get an A. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS. Waste of time and money.

Okay, now a lot of people say that she's mean/crazy/unfair, this is not true. I admit she is hard, and I admit that she gave me the only B i've ever received, but behind the scenes shes a nice person and its not impossible to get an A, as long as you work really hard.

This woman should not be a professor.  SHe is a basket case who needs to get therapy for herself.  She is the worse professor I have ever had and she does not know her materials at all.  In addition she is prejudice and completely biased. I would never recommend her to anyone .

Dr. Austin was a patient teacher. She definitely knew what she was talking about. She is willing to stay after class and speak with you for hours about any personal issues. Her tests are fair, but you do need to be well prepared for them. Don't get on her bad side, because it won't go very well for you throughout the semester. Just do what is expec

She is the ultimate dragon lady! I swear I've seen fire come out of that evil mouth of hers. Now I know I'm a good writer, but this one finds something wrong no matter what...do yourself a favor and avoid at all costs! Your sanity it worth it!

She was the worst professor I ever had.I had her for 2 classes..First social psych and then experimental psych. I wasted $3,000 on a summer class where I learned nothing.She was barely in class & we were expected to know everything even if she didn't teach it.  She does not care about her students nor there to work with you if you need help!
Gave whole class imcompletes

The class was hard - and Sue is demanding.  But - you're in college - so if you want a teacher to spoon feed you go back to pre-school.  She is fair, kind, available to her students, and funny as hell!

The worst most boreing class I've ever taken.  She was always unprepared and disorganized. Her lessons were off topic and boreing.  The assigned reading were unintereting and very diffiucult to read.  her tests were vauge and impossible.  She was rude to students who did not share her views.  It appeared she liked to talk to hear her own voice.
Not nice

sue is a dynamic, down to earth women without pretention.  although my class was at nassau community college on saturdays,i am certain her methods are consistant in all her places of work. Just very genuine and true to her feelings.  If you participate,and do your best without any bull, she knows and will go the extra mile for you.  thanks sue.

She is such a doll.  Don't come in thinking negative, if you do then you will create your own nutty things.  She is extremely nice and easy to get along with, plus, open questions how easy can it get!
No Comments
No Comments

Easy tests but she has interesting stories. I espicially love the one where she said she threw up in class and turned around then swallowed it.. just wanted i wanted to hear. And make sure you dont park in handicapped spots.. she'll kick ur ass
sue rocks! she may be a hard prof, but if you actually work and aren't a lazy ass, you can learn so much from her.  she's the best!
there are not enough negative things i can say about this wack job
this lady is so nuts that she should be locked up

Shes hysterical, all she does in class is try to apply the material with humor so you remember it!! She is great, BUT I would never take experimental with her bc I hear shes NUTS.  My favorite prof at adelphi so far!

she is a nice teacher personality wise, but not good at teaching social psychology. her lectures have nothing to do with the exams. you have to do all the readings before tests, and she will not curve or explain properply what is needed of you.

great teacher, her tests are very simple if you study ur notes and take good notes. her labs are hard and she is a tough grader on them, so be precise. she is funny and sarcastic, i'd def take another class with Sue.

She is nice and easy in all her other classes, the only one where she is a real B*$!H and will make you work your ass off is in here Experimental class..the work-load is non-stop and you have to be precise about everything in the lab!! even one missed comma will get you a lower grade, no kidding

I heard that she was a mean prof. but I found that she was the total opposite.  Lets you use a cheat sheet for the tests and explains everything clearly.  If you don't act like an ass, she won't be mean.
I found her to be very unorganized. she was always late to class. Her test were not easy.

Definitly knows her stuff, very intelligent. However, not very respectful to students. Sometimes gets mad when asked questions (thats what she's there for will someone tell her). Constantly late-but u cant be.Overall, you'll do well if you study and take notes. Fair grader,would take her again. i am
worst prof i've ever had...absolutely horrible. pathetic stories and even more pathetic person
RUN FROM HER, SHES CRAZY AND WILL MAKE YOUR LIFE A LIVING HELL, MAYBE SHE JUST NEEDS A MAN IN HER LIFE TO MAKE HER MORE PLEASENT....SHES HORRIBLE
No Comments

I had her my freshman year. She isn't the easiest, but not toughest. She's not as mean as everyone describes. She a fair teacher who doesnt take bs. Dont be late, dont fall asleep and she wouldn't be mean. Just take good notes, and you'll be fine.
I HATE HER SHE IS THE WORST STAY AWAY!!!!!!!!!!!Take Seizer instead
Worst college experience ever!! She made two people cry and was absolutly heartless. She made the class feel stupid was extremely arrogant. Stay away!
One of my favorite teachers. I'm aboout to take my third class with her. Very fair grader. She cares about what she's teaching and is interesting to listen to.

I'm not sure what everyone here is talking about.  If you work hard and study for the tests you'll do fine.  She IS very down to earth as long as she sees you working hard. ----why was my rating made about her last year mysteriously deleted?
She wasnt a bad teacher. Seemed like a real person, but didnt really care about her students. Overall she was fair, but nothing special.

STAY AWAY FROM AUSTIN!!!! she is the biggest **** you'll ever meet.She acts like a complete **** if a studnet needs her help.She needs to get laid big time.PLease quit!!! you would be doing AU and NY a favor.

Austin sucks!! She is by far the worst teacher at Adelphi. She's mean and unhelpful, she gets mad if you ask her for help. She wears turtle necks in 500 degree weather and wonders why she's dying of heat.  Stay away from Austin's class!

She is not down to earth, she is below the earth, straight from the pits of hell. She doesn't belong in a classroom at all, she belongs in the military instead making life hell for soldiers instead of students. She is miserable and negative. Stay away!!!!
STAY AWAY! WORST PROF EVER!!
horrible professor. rude, extremely anal, arrogant, unfair grader. worst teacher i have ever had by far! my avdice would be to AVOID her classes.
she is a good, fair teacher...her sidetracks/jokes are annoying but shes a good teacher
No Comments
she's ok. nuthing great
Worst teacher ever.  She is rude and grades unfairly.  This class was horrible and so were her jokes.  I recommend avoiding a class with her.
She's great...down to earth & fun...she definitely makes class interesting!
No Comments
Her lessons are interesting, and she makes you laugh.  She is a fair grader, and very willing to help any of her students.  She is very down to earth.
SHe is a great, teacher, very clear and fair, ther should be more like her!
She's awesome. Take her!
This woman speaks the way it is. She's such a tough cookie. I admire her so much. I can't wait to take another course with her. She's so experienced in her field and she's funny!

Professor Frey is great!  Prior to taking the class I read the comments on here and was honestly scared, but I found her class to be one of my favorites at Adelphi.  I did not find her condescending at all - she can be a jokester, but most students know how to take her jokes.  Take her class!!
she will loose papers throughout the semester, make sure you keep a copy of everything

Her "story time" brings a lot of knowledge and experience with it. She is a straight shooter and sometimes her criticism is hard to take, but believe me, you will be a better teacher/person. I can equate it to listening to your grandparent. You think the advice is stupid but when they are gone,you realize how practical/useful the advice was.

Her "story time" brings a lot of knowledge and experience with it. She is a straight shooter and sometimes her criticism is hard to take, but believe me, you will be a better teacher/person. I can equate it to listening to your grandparent. You think the advice is stupid but when they are gone,you realize how practical/useful the advice was.

Professor Frey is the worst Professor I took at Adelphi this semester. She is condescending, has her favorites and forgets to actually teach the last two months of the semester! She likes to ridicule her students and treats them as if they were stupid.
Worst teacher ever.  Rude, condescending, didn't teach a single thing!  Waste of time, even though I got an A.  Wish I had spent my 3 grand on something better than this...

Looking back at my college experience, I can truly say that Prof. Frey was the BEST professor in Adelphi.  You might not appreciate her style/content of her lessons now; but when you get into "the real world" you will appreciate that Prof Frey is the only one who taught you the pertinent information you will use.
Good teacher. Doesn't use the textbook. Gives tests based on her lessons in class only.

Absolutely wonderful woman.  She is an educated, worldly and knowledgeable professor who discusses topics in detail.  Many valuable lessons can be learned in her experience.  Provides clear method of grading and fair quizzes that reflect notes.  If you attend class, take notes and listen you will do very well.  I would take more classes with her.

Wow, what a waste of time. She is unprepared, unclear, condescending and never gives anyone a chance to respond or say anything. One of the worst professors I ever had & I would NEVER consider taking another class with her.  I got an A, but I didn't learn a thing.  Same with everyone else in the class.
She is an awesome teacher.  She teaches you about everything, is flexible, smart, and willing to help and discuss. She is difficult but very fair.  Take Her!
Pass her horrible self-made quizzes or it doesn't matter how many A's you get on all other projects
nice professor... very qualified and knew her stuff... she's got plenty to say and is a fair grader.... do the reading- you'll learn much more than lecture time

Wow. I can't believe I spent 2000 dollars for this class. Talk about lack of instruction. You may think she knows what she is talking about, but if you are already a teacher like myself, this class was a waste of time. Her grading system is completely unclear, I would never take another class with h
really great teacher, tough lady though.  very fair, and totally knows what she is talking about.
knows what she is teaching
Ambiguous in her instruction, Nice lady AFTER CLASS..
really knows her stuff-and teaches it!
Her Socratic method can be frustrating, but shes GREAT!!!
